##KEYWORDS('gradient', 'vector', 'field')

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1, 10);
$b = random(1, 10);
$c = random(1, 10);
$d = random(1, 10);

$ans1i = "2*$a*x";
$ans1j = "2*$b*y";

$ans2i = "($c*x^($c -1))*y^($d)";
$ans2j = "($d*y^($d -1))*x^($c)";

$ans3i = "$a";
$ans3j = "$b";

$ans4i = "$a";
$ans4j = "$b";
$ans4k = "$c";

$ans5i = "2*$a*x";
$ans5j = "2*$b*y";
$ans5k = "2*$c*z";

BEGIN_TEXT
$PAR
Compute the gradient vector fields of the following functions:
$PAR
A. \( f(x, y) = $a x^2 + $b y^2 \) 
   $BR \( \nabla f(x, y) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf i + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf j \)
$PAR
B. \( f(x, y) = x^{$c} y^{$d}, \) 
   $BR \( \nabla f(x, y) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf i + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf j \)
$PAR
C. \( f(x, y) = $a x + $b y \) 
   $BR \( \nabla f(x, y) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf i + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf j \)
$PAR
D. \( f(x, y, z) = $a x + $b y + $c z \) 
   $BR \( \nabla f(x, y) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf i + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf j + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf k \)
$PAR
E. \( f(x, y, z) = $a x^2 + $b y^2 + $c z^2 \) 
   $BR \( \nabla f(x, y, z) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf i + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf j + \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \bf k \)
END_TEXT
#A.
ANS(function_cmp($ans1i));
ANS(function_cmp($ans1j, 'y'));

#B.
ANS(multivar_function_cmp($ans2i,2));
ANS(multivar_function_cmp($ans2j,2));

#C.
ANS(function_cmp($ans3i));
ANS(function_cmp($ans3j, 'y'));

#D.
ANS(function_cmp($ans4i));
ANS(function_cmp($ans4j, 'y'));
ANS(function_cmp($ans4k, 'z'));

#E.
ANS(function_cmp($ans5i));
ANS(function_cmp($ans5j, 'y'));
ANS(function_cmp($ans5k, 'z'));

ENDDOCUMENT();
